Ariana Grande-Butera is an American singer, songwriter and actress. She is known for her expansive four-octave vocal range.
Blackpink (블랙핑크) is a South Korean girl group formed by YG Entertainment, consisting of members Jisoo, Jennie, Rosé, and Lisa.
BTS (방탄소년단 Bangtan Sonyeondan) is a seven member South Korean boy band that began formation in 2010 and debuted in 2013 under Big Hit.
Coldplay are a British rock band formed in London in 1996. Vocalist and pianist Chris, guitarist Jonny, bassist Guy, and drummer Will.
Ashley Nicolette Frangipane (born September 29, 1994), known professionally as Halsey is an American singer, songwriter, and activist.
Maroon 5 is an American pop rock band from Los Angeles. It currently consists of vocalist Adam Levine and the others.
One Direction are an English-Irish pop boy band formed in London in 2010. The group are composed of Niall, Liam, Harry and Louis.
SF9 (에스에프나인) is a South Korean boy group formed by FNC Entertainment. Consisting of nine members, the group debuted on October 5, 2016.
